{
  "text": "scnRNA selection has not been investigated. To clarify this relationship, we aimed to analyze the turnover of earlyscnRNAs during artificial epigenetic inhibition of DNA elimination [CITATION_1] , where the introduction of an IES to the MAC (Figure 2A , i) selectively inhibits the elimination of the corresponding IES from the new MAC in the sexual progeny (Figure 2A, iii) . It has been predicted [CITATION_2] , but not demonstrated, that this epigenetic effect is mediated by the degradation of early-scnRNAs complementary to the introduced IES via scnRNA selection (Figure 2A , ii).",
